Rule 1: The T stage for breast cancer is determined by the size of the primary tumor.
Rule 2: T1 stage corresponds to a tumor size of 2 cm or less.
Rule 3: T2 stage corresponds to a tumor size of more than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm.
Rule 4: T3 stage corresponds to a tumor size of more than 5 cm.
Rule 5: T4 stage corresponds to a tumor of any size with direct extension to the chest wall or skin.
Rule 6: Ignore any substaging information while determining the T stage.
